.\" -*- nroff -*-
.TH NORDUGRIDMAP 8 "@DATE@" "NorduGrid ARC @VERSION@" "NorduGrid System Managers Manual"
.SH NAME
nordugridmap \- ARC grid-mapfile generator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nordugridmap
[\fB-t\fR, \fB--test\fR] [\fB-c\fR, \fB--config\fR \fIFILE\fR] [\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
nordugridmap is usually run as a crontab entry in order to automatically generate mapfile(s). For configuration information consult tne Nordugruid ARC documentation and the arc.conf.reference
.PP
The following applies for [vo] blocks in arc.conf :
.PP
For
   "source=file://some/file.txt"

if file.txt is in the grid-mapfile syntax:

   /c=dk/cn=some user/... some_unix_user
.PP
the nordugridmap utility will IGNORE the mapped_unixid field in 
the [vo] configuration block for that specific line of the file in favour
of some_unix_user.
In other words, mapped_unixid in arc.conf has no effect on an entry
in file.txt if some_unix_user is specified for that entry. 
For DNs without some_unix_user, the utility will use the one specified in 
[vo]'s mapped_unixid command.
.PP
For
   "source=http://some.server.com/some/file.txt"

file.txt can simply be a list of DN's.
.PP
Note that when parsing remote URLs such as https://, the target file is expected to 
contain a single column with DNs. This is because a remote location might not be 
aware of any local unix users (as a local gridmap file would).

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-test\fR
Does not actually create grid-mapfile(s), but perform test run in debug mode.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config \fIFILE\fR
Specifies the configuration file to be used. By default the /etc/arc.conf is used. nordugridmap utilize [nordugridmap] section for general options fine-tunung and processes all the [vo] blocks from the config.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show help options
.PP
